      "blocked_reason": "Texture/surface coherency: make_dog reads the octave data array via tex2DLayered and gets stale/zero after aa::vert wrote it via surf2DLayeredwrite (an immediate surf2DLayeredread returns the fresh value), so the DoG pyramid is all-zero and 0 features are detected. HIP linear-filter texture and wave64 warp-packing bugs already fixed (determinism restored, no -nan). Under investigation whether this is a HIP runtime bug (texture cache not invalidated at the launch boundary; CUDA guarantees cross-launch coherency), a CDNA detail, or app intra-kernel-coherence reliance. Fix candidates: read make_dog/extrema from the surface, recreate the texture after the blur, or invalidate. WIP preserved at jeffdaily/popsift @ moat-port.",
